# Git Workflow

## Branching

- `main`: production-ready, always green
- `feature/<requirement-id>`: single feature branch per requirement
- Each execute Task uses an isolated **git worktree** (not branch)

## Worktree Isolation (Required)

Every Task in /execute must use a dedicated git worktree:
```
git worktree add .worktrees/task-<n> <base-branch>
```
This prevents cross-task interference during parallel implementation.

## Commit Etiquette

- One commit per logical change (not per file)
- Commit messages: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`
- Scope: the skill name (e.g., `execute`, `spec`)

## Workflow State

- `.workflow-state.json` is git-ignored (session-local)
- Execution reports under `orch-spec/` are committed as artifacts
- Never commit worktree directories (`.worktrees/`)

## Safety

- No force push to main
- No --no-verify (never skip hooks)
- Always create new commits, never amend shared history
